Pathway.Name: Sphingolipid metabolism: integrated pathway
Pathway.Comment: This pathway is inspired by the Lipidmaps>Sphingolipids pathway (all chain lengths) [https://lipidmaps.org/resources/pathways/vanted.php]. Sphingolipids are a class of lipids, which act as signal transduction and cell recognition molecules. This pathway shows all different tail lengths and their conversions into specific products. All products are annotated with lipid-specific identifiers (if available). The general overview pathway can be found [https://www.wikipathways.org/index.php/Pathway:WP4344 here].
This pathway was inferred from Mus musculus pathway [WP4690_107209.gpml] with a 95.0% conversion rate.
